    <!--
    Figma exports each rect with rotate(-7°) around its OWN top-left. The paths (notch, squiggles,
    chat bubbles) have rotation already baked into their coordinates.

    We wrap everything in one -7° group (pivot = body top-left) so the clip-path and rects can stay
    unrotated. Rects that had a different SVG pivot are placed at their inverse-rotated local
    position (they all landed on clean offsets: screen=body+3px inset, outline=body+0.75px inset,
    input bar=body+6/70.5px). The already-baked paths go in a nested +7° group to cancel out.
